'''Shusko Station''' was a [[Mining/Legends|mining]] operation in the [[Gam Tim'nisi asteroid belt]]. It was owned by [[Kelko]]'s family, who also owned several other businesses throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].

The clan to which Kelko's [[Parent/Legends|father]] belonged was at war with the clan of [[Gender/Legends|his]] mother, so they both had to run away. A third clan [[Death/Legends|assassinated]] the young couple, as the war of these two clans was of their interest. However, the father's and the mother's clans, worried about the disappearance of the young couple, united against a common foe, annihilated the third clan and made peace.

A member of the clan, [[Govenni]], searched for their long-lost relative and his own grandson, Kelko. He found him working as a freelance [[Technician/Legends|mechanic]] and [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] at Shusko Station, aided only by a [[WED00-88|second-hand droid]]. Govenni revealed to Kelko details about his heritage and told him that he could choose at least one of the family businesses. Kelko decided to keep Shusko Station instead of other profitable businesses like [[Casino/Legends|casinos]] and resorts.

After Kelko took over, Shusko Station quickly became one of the most profitable small mining operations on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]].

